# Trivy vulnerability suppressions — keep each entry narrow and time-bound.
#
# Format:
#   <CVE-ID>
# or an expiry-gated entry:
#   <CVE-ID> exp:YYYY-MM-DD
#
# Every entry MUST have a comment above it explaining:
#   1. Where the vulnerability lives (package, path).
#   2. Why the fix is not available from this repo.
#   3. What would make us drop the suppression.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# codesteward-taint binary — Go stdlib CVEs
#
# The bundled /usr/local/bin/codesteward-taint binary is downloaded from the
# upstream Codesteward/codesteward-taint release. The only published release
# (v0.1.0) was built with Go 1.22.12 and inherits a set of Go stdlib CVEs.
# These cannot be fixed from this repo — they require the upstream project
# to tag a new release built with a patched Go toolchain.
#
# TODO: drop these ignores once upstream ships a release built with Go ≥ 1.26.2
# (tracked in codesteward-taint — see its release pipeline).
# Until then, operators who do not need taint analysis can build with
#   --build-arg TAINT_VERSION=none
# which removes the binary and makes the scan pass without this file.
CVE-2025-68121
